---
import Default from '../layouts/Default.astro';

const title = 'Technical review | TARIDE Foundation';
const description = 'The foundation actively solicits feedback from telecom, security, privacy, and DID/SSI practitioners.';
---

<Default title={title} description={description} pageId="review">
  <div class="container-reading">

    <span class="page-eyebrow">Get involved</span>
    <h1 class="page-title">Technical review</h1>
    <p class="page-lede">
      The TARIDE specification is published in public, in draft, and explicitly seeking review. Four audiences are addressed directly.
    </p>

    <h2>Who the foundation is asking</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Telecom providers</strong>:credential lifecycle, subscriber binding, registry interfaces.</li>
      <li><strong>Security researchers</strong>:threat model, cryptographic constructions, attack taxonomy.</li>
      <li><strong>Privacy advocates and regulators</strong>:GDPR alignment, unlinkability, retention.</li>
      <li><strong>DID and SSI practitioners</strong>:standards alignment, resolver architecture, interoperability.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What kind of feedback is useful</h2>
    <p>
      Specific, scoped, and falsifiable. The most useful contributions identify an assumption that does not hold, propose a concrete change, or flag a downstream implication the foundation has not considered. Endorsements without substance are less helpful than well-aimed criticism.
    </p>

    <h2>How to send it</h2>
    <p>
      Two channels:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>For specific document or section feedback: an issue or pull request on <a href="https://github.com/TARIDE-org/docs" rel="noopener">TARIDE-org/docs</a>.</li>
      <li>For broader conversations, an introduction, or to flag adjacent work: <a href="mailto:info@taride.org">info@taride.org</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What you can expect back</h2>
    <p>
      Acknowledgement within five working days. Substantive responses to substantive review. The foundation publishes a feedback summary at the close of each review window; named reviewers are credited unless they ask not to be.
    </p>

  </div>
</Default>
